environment.model.roadusers.vehicles

Class FamilySedan_Vehicle

  • java.lang.Object
    • environment.model.roadusers.vehicles.Vehicle
      • environment.model.roadusers.vehicles.FamilySedan_Vehicle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public final class FamilySedan_Vehicle
extends Vehicle
    The FamilySedan class is a subclass of the vehicle class, which models a Family sedan.

    The FamilySedan uses the Vehicle.size and Vehicle.tankSize attributes from the Vehicle class, which are initialised upon creation of the FamilySedan.

    The FamilySedan class cannot be extended.

    • Constructor Detail

      • FamilySedan_Vehicle

        public FamilySedan_Vehicle()
        Create a new FamilySedan.

        Initialise a FamilySedan object by invoking the Vehicle constructor, where the Vehicle.size is set as UNIT_SIZE (1.5) and the Vehicle.tankSize is set to a minimum of MIN_TANK_SIZE (12), with a range of TANK_SIZE_RANGE (7).

        size = RNG.nextInt(7) + 12

      • FamilySedan_Vehicle

        private FamilySedan_Vehicle(double size,
                            int tankSize,
                            int fuelLevel,
                            FuelType fuelType)
        Create a new instance of the FamilySedan_Vehicle class with a specified size, tank size, fuel level and fuel type.

        This constructor is only used for creating clones of the FamilySedan_Vehicle using the Vehicle#getCloneConstructor() method.

        Parameters:
        size - The size of the FamilySedan_Vehicle.
        tankSize - The tank size of the FamilySedan_Vehicle.
        fuelLevel - The current fuel level of the FamilySedan_Vehicle.
        fuelType - The fuel type of the FamilySedan_Vehicle.

    • Method Detail

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Check if an object is equal to the FamilySedan.

        Compare an object against a FamilySedan if the object is an instance of the FamilySedan class, then the Vehicle.equals(Object) method will determine if the object is equal to the FamilySedan, otherwise, if the object is not an instance of the FamilySedan class, the object cannot be equal to any FamilySedan.

        Overrides:
        equals in class Vehicle
        Parameters:
        o - The object to be tested for equality against.
        Returns:
        true if the object is and instance of the FamilySedan class, and the Vehicle.size and Vehicle.tankSize of the object are equal to the FamilySedan; otherwise false.
